diff:1378235789:1378235789:=1,44d0%0a%3c !Game Interface Help%0a%3c %0a%3c !!!!Player Interface Help%0a%3c *[[#RS|The Request System]]%0a%3c *[[#BB|Bluebooking]]%0a%3c %0a%3c !!The Request System%0a%3c The Request System is designed to facilitate communication between you and your Storyteller(s). For those who are familiar with "Character Threads," this is the bigger, better, shinier version!%0a%3c %0a%3c !!!Submitting a Request%0a%3c -> 1) Create a request - Give it a title and put the body of the request in. %0a%3c -->''After you create the request, it will be in a "New Status" that is not yet submitted to STs so that you can gather any relevant supplemental information.''%0a%3c ->2) Attach other requests, bluebook entries, dice rolls, or other characters to your request as applicable.%0a%3c -->''Attaching another character is a way to indicate who has been helping you with that particular request. They will see your request on their dashboard and have the ability to sign off that they have actually been doing what you indicated.''%0a%3c -> 3) Submit your request to the STs. This will move it to a submitted status. %0a%3c -->''You can still attach entries to your request while it's in the 'Submitted' status.%0a%3c %0a%3c !!!Storyteller Follow Up%0a%3c -> 1) The ST views your request on their dashboard. They can opt to Approve, Deny, or Return a request. %0a%3c -->''Approve or Deny - this will return the request to the player for them to close. This is so that a player can know what happened with their request.''%0a%3c -->''Return - This returns the request back to the player to update for whatever reason.''%0a%3c ->2)The ST can (and should) provide a note to the request when they take an action on it.%0a%3c %0a%3c !!!Resolving a Request%0a%3c -> 1) Review and Close your character's Approved or Rejected request.%0a%3c -> 2) Update Requests that have been returned and resubmit.%0a%3c %0a%3c !!!Types of Requests%0a%3c * '''Action''': Submit to request ST attention to an action your character wishes to take. A common example is researching a plot lead.%0a%3c * '''Sanction''': After creating a character, submit a request for your character to be sanctioned. This is in lieu of FPMing an ST.%0a%3c * '''XP Spend''': When you're reading to put points into your character.%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#BB]]%0a%3c !!Bluebooking%0a%3c The Bluebook is your personal character record, and where you keep track of your character's achievements, progress towards goals, participation in scenes, and important events. For those familiar with "Character Threads," this equates to the non-request use.%0a%3c %0a%3c Q: What format should I use?%0a%3c A: There is not a specific format that is required of a Bluebook, and in fact, it is very likely that you are the only person who will read most of your posts.  You can make your posts a weekly list of things your character accomplished, a paragraph summary of every scene you've been in, a quick few sentences about something you want to remember, or even an In Character journal. %0a%3c %0a%3c Q: If an ST isn't going to read it, why do it?%0a%3c A: In general, you don't have to. This isn't a requirement of remaining sanctioned, however your individual venue Storytellers may require proof of justification for an XP spend. Bluebook posts can be attached to requests made through the Request system to back up your request.%0a%3c %0a%3c Q: Can I search my Bluebook posts for references to something I'm trying to make a request for?%0a%3c A: Not right now, so its strongly recommended you keep this in mind when naming your entries as the name will be what is visible in the list.%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
